    "problemStatement": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Height and Distance is a branch of trigonometry used to find the height, distance, or position of objects by using angles and trigonometric ratios like sine, cosine, and tangent. It helps us measure things that are difficult to measure directly, such as the height of a building, the distance of a ship from the shore, or the elevation of a mountain.</span></p><figure class=\"image\"><img alt=\"angle_of_elevation\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation.webp\" srcset=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation.webp 800w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation-100.webp 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation-200.webp 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation-300.webp 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation-660.webp 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20260516101851948443/angle_of_elevation-768.webp 768w\" width=\"800\"/><figcaption> </figcaption></figure><h2 id=\"foundations\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Foundations</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Master the core trigonometry concepts that form the base for understanding and solving Heights &amp; Distances problems.</span></p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\"><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-introduction-to-trigonometry-class-10-maths-notes-chapter-8\"><span>Introduction to Trigonometry</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-sin-cos-tan-formula\"><span>Sin, Cos, Tan Values</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-pythagoras-theorem\"><span>Pythagoras Theorem </span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trigonometry-table\"><span>Trigonometry Table</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trick-to-remember-trigonometric-table\"><span>Trick to Remember Trigonometric Table</span></a></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trigonometric-ratios-of-some-specific-angles\"><span>Trigonometric Ratios of Specific Angles</span></a></li><li value=\"7\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trigonometry-formulas-class-10\"><span>Trigonometry Formulas</span></a></li><li value=\"8\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-trigonometric-identities-class-10\"><span>Trigonometric Identities</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"core-concepts-of-heights-distances\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Core Concepts</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Learn the key concepts of Heights &amp; Distances that are essential for solving angle-based measurement problems.</span></p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\"><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-introduction-to-height-and-distance\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Introduction to Height and Distance</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-angle-of-elevation\"><span>Angle of Elevation</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-angle-of-depression\"><span>Angle of Depression</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"applications-of-trigonometry-in-real-life\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Applications of Trigonometry</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Explore how trigonometry is applied in real-world fields such as navigation, architecture, aviation, engineering, and surveying.</span></p><ul class=\"[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3\"><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-applications-of-trigonometry\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Applications of Trigonometry in Real Life</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude-applications-of-trigonometric-functions\"><span>Real Life Applications of Trigonometric Functions</span></a></li></ul>",
